{
  "complexity_details": "The \"Fourth National Communication and First Biennial Transparency Report\" activity is technically complex, requiring comprehensive GHG inventory development, tracking NDC implementation, assessing climate change impacts, and compiling/submitting reports to the UNFCCC. It necessitates significant capacity building in data collection, analysis, and institutional strengthening to overcome a stated \"lack of a coordinated team of support and climate finance expertise.\" Its successful execution is critical for Montenegro to meet its national sustainable development goals and international commitments.",
  "how_integrated_description": "The activity is deeply and cohesively integrated into Montenegro's national climate change strategy and its international obligations under the United Nations Framework Convention on Climate Change (UNFCCC) and the Paris Agreement. It directly supports the country's Nationally Determined Contributions (NDC2), contributes to enhancing climate change governance, and fortifies institutional capacity for long-term climate monitoring and reporting. It is a crucial component of Montenegro's broader, ongoing national program for climate action and compliance with international environmental agreements."
}

{
  "complexity_details": "This activity, \"Protection of Environment and Biodiversity in Jordan II,\" presents high technical and institutional complexity. It requires developing IT-based monitoring systems for environmental metadata (web portal, e-readiness/IT masterplan) and hazardous waste. MoEnv's limited power, staff, and budget necessitate extensive capacity building. Risks include political shifts, human capacity limits, and stakeholder cooperation issues.",
