{
  "complexity_details": "The activity is moderately complex, involving significant environmental rehabilitation (75 hectares of dune cordon), water resource management (returning 19 million liters), and a multi-faceted approach to achieve diverse benefits including flood/erosion control, water quality improvement, carbon sequestration, and habitat preservation. It also incorporates socio-economic development through an agricultural micro-project for rural women, educational and awareness-raising components, and ecotourism promotion. The project addresses critical wetland degradation due to anthropogenic pressures and operates under a robust legal framework with strict financial, risk management, and social/environmental sustainability standards, requiring careful coordination and diverse expertise for successful implementation.",
